Kidding aside, damage shields are good whenever there are no stacking issues, and you have the spell gem to spend on the thing.  When in doubt, use it   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tegasie>Tegasie</A> at: 6/16/03 9:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=l1ndara>L1ndara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 230<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 9:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are Our DS line a waste?</span><hr size=1>   115 mana is a lot for a 5pt shield.  For a tiny bit more mana you can Ice Shock for over 300 damage (at level 34.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilsainsilverback>Pilsain Silverback</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 937<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 10:23 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are Our DS line a waste?</span><hr size=1> That's the question I'm hoping to get answered here...<br>
