 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gyorg@graffeswizardcompilation>Gyorg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 11:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> DS</span><hr size=1> I would be interested in seeing what would be the highest DS you could achieve, if you had access to lvl 65s of all classes. Which stacks with which , in otherwords. There are all these mobs out there that flurry and rampage, a high DS could add up to considerable damage and make them pay for those extra attacks.<br>
Anyone seen such a list?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=acillatemzoso>Acillatem Zoso</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 235<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 12:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DS</span><hr size=1> I'm sure it's probably different now with PoP out - but before that I had approx 84 point damage shield via potions and thorns.<br>
<br>
Kilva's Blistering Flesh = 1/2 your level + 5 I believe (been a while - but thats relatively close).<br>
<br>
Ro's Breath (yes our epic thing) stacks with Kilvas Blistering Flesh, and then you have thorns.<br>
<br>
Never got a chance to add in MAG dmg shield - but if I'm not mistaken Ro's Breath is the MAG version adn wouldnt stack.<br>
<br>
Anywayz end result was an 84 point dmg shield and I was level 60 at the time pre-PoP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pedidustyboots>Pedi Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 934<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/03 12:19 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DS</span><hr size=1> DS is totally worth it. I realize that it's tedious to recast it for every fight, but that is what druids and mages have to do. I think druids and mages have longer durations, but they still have to recast DS often. Tanks love them.<br>
<br>
As far as I know, you don't get aggro from DS. It's like invisible damage. If a mob beats himself to death on the DS and no one else has hurt the mob, the mob will just poof -- you won't get experience for killing it. Hence it being invisible damage. If you do ONE point of damage to the mob (via spells or weapon) and the DS does the rest of the damage, you will still get the XP for it. Hope that makes sense.<br>
<br>
BTW, Whiz wanted to duel my cleric to see if he could beat me. He got a very nice element of surprise because I couldn't figure out why my hammer pet was dying repeatedly since the pets weren't targetable. I knew that you could kill the pets by outrunning them, but my pet was actually taking damage. Turns out that Whiz was using his own DS (plus the 8th coldain ring) to kill it. That isn't something other classes think about. We don't really realize that wizards have the ability to cast DS or we just don't expect them to actually use it.<br>
<br>
